sents case studies of esoteric writing in the work of four of the first kabbalistic authors—Abraham ben David, Isaac the Blind, Ezra ben Solomon, and Asher ben David—and thereby helps recast our understanding of the earliest stages of kabbalistic literary history.The book will interest scholars in Jewish mysticism and Jewish philosophy, as well as those working in medieval Jewish history. Throughout, Jonathan V. Dauber has endeavored to write an accessible work that does not require extensive prior knowledge of kabbalistic thought. Accordingly, it finds points of contact between scholars of various religious traditions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aHistory of Jewish People and Culture. 4aInterdisciplinary-Jewish Studies. 4aReligion-Judaism. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / Kabbalah & Mysticism.2bisacsh  aAbraham b. David.  aAsher b. David.  aEsotericism.  aEzra b. Solomon of Gerona.  aIsaac the Blind.  aKabbalah.  aLeo Strauss.  aSecrecy.  aanagram.  acode.  aliterary device.  amedieval Jewish history.  amysticism.  aoccult.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022 Englishz978311099454408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022z9783110994537oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076767440uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/9781512822762?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781512822762423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781512822762/original  a978-3-11-07